#import "../../macros/core.typ": *

== Core notation

The core module provides reusable alphabets, operators, and delimiter helpers.

=== Blackboard bold

$bbA, bbB, bbC, bbD, bbE, bbF, bbG, bbH, bbI, bbJ, bbK, bbL, bbM$

$bbN, bbO, bbP, bbQ, bbR, bbS, bbT, bbU, bbV, bbW, bbX, bbY, bbZ$

=== Calligraphic letters

$cA, cB, cC, cD, cE, cF, cG, cH, cI, cJ, cK, cL, cM$

$cN, cO, cP, cQ, cR, cS, cT, cU, cV, cW, cX, cY, cZ$

=== Operators

$argmax_(x in bbR) f(x)$, $argmin_(x in bbR) f(x)$, $rank(A)$, $trace(A)$, $diag(v)$, $span(S)$, $supp(f)$, $dom(f)$, $codom(f)$, $img(f)$, and $ker(f)$.

=== Delimiters

$abs(x)$, $norm(x)$, $inner(x, y)$, $setof(x in X: P(x))$, $ceil(x)$, and $floor(x)$.
